Subject: [liste-egc] Medical Information Retrieval Tutorial at AIME 2019
 conference

(Apologies for cross-posting)
MEDICAL INFORMATION RETRIEVAL TUTORIAL
AIME 2019 - Poznan, Poland
26th of June 2019

Presenters: Prof. Lynda Tamine (Universit=C3=A9 Paul Sabatier, France) =
and Dr Lorraine Goeuriot (Universit=C3=A9 Grenoble Alpes, France)

This tutorial will firstly introduce the IR basics and the potential of =
IR in the clinical informatics community, explore the peculiarities of =
medical IR including health-related queries and tasks and knowledge =
resources. Secondly, we will focus on the techniques and methods that =
allow tackling medical IR challenges such as semantic gap, negation and =
result appraisal. We will cover both the symbolic semantics through the =
use of external resources (eg. UMLS, MeSH, Gene Ontology) and the =
distributional semantics relying on words collocations in the corpus =
including learning approaches of representation of concepts and =
documents. Thirdly, we will provide basics of IR evaluation benchmarking =
and develop a roadmap on the main evaluation campaigns existing in =
medical IR and then report the key lessons. Finally, we summarize the =
research findings in the area and outline the key open research =
questions.
More information can be found on our website: =
http://mrim.imag.fr/User/lorraine.goeuriot/tuto-medical-ir/

Registration and general information about AIME 2019 can be found here: =
http://aime19.aimedicine.info/index.php

We=E2=80=99re looking forward to meeting you in AIME!
Lynda & Lorraine

